14
00:00:48.050 --> 00:00:51.800
challenges. First, oncogenic drivers remain difficult to drug,

15
00:00:52.020 --> 00:00:54.380
particularly transcription factors and RAS family members.

16
00:00:55.580 --> 00:00:59.290
Second, resistance is inevitable, often emerging through

17
00:00:59.290 --> 00:01:01.390
pathway rewiring or adapted signaling.

18
00:01:02.360 --> 00:01:06.030
And third, many cancers depend not on single proteins, but on

19
00:01:06.040 --> 00:01:09.990
dynamic multi-protein complexes and cellular states that are not easily

20
00:01:10.040 --> 00:01:11.840
addressed with traditional inhibitors.

21
00:01:12.470 --> 00:01:16.300
So these challenges have catalyzed a major evolution in how we think

22
00:01:16.380 --> 00:01:18.060
about targeting cancer.

23
00:01:19.020 --> 00:01:22.480
What we will see in this session is a shift in strategy

24
00:01:23.300 --> 00:01:26.600
from direct inhibition to pathway exploitation,

25
00:01:27.220 --> 00:01:30.530
from single targets to coordinated system-level disruption,

26
00:01:31.240 --> 00:01:35.190
from canonical drug targets to target RNA, protein complexes, and

27
00:01:35.240 --> 00:01:38.990
immune regulators, and from passive delivery to tumor-selective uptick

28
00:01:39.140 --> 00:01:39.800
mechanisms.

29
00:01:41.060 --> 00:01:43.710
The talks today highlight three major emerging

30
00:01:44.360 --> 00:01:46.180
paradigms in targeted therapy.

31
00:01:47.500 --> 00:01:51.400
One, exploiting the tumor-specific biology for drug delivery and targeting,

32
00:01:52.160 --> 00:01:55.790
targeting the undruggable through non-canonical modalities, and

33
00:01:55.860 --> 00:01:58.880
leveraging the ubiquitin system and immune modulation.

34
00:01:59.140 --> 00:02:02.500
So across these diverse approaches, a unifying concept

35
00:02:02.900 --> 00:02:03.600
emerges

36
00:02:04.400 --> 00:02:07.860
where we're no longer limited to inhibiting oncogenic proteins.

37
00:02:08.581 --> 00:02:12.180
We can now redirect cellular machinery, exploit tumor-specific

38
00:02:12.260 --> 00:02:16.140
biology, and engineer entirely new therapeutic modalities.

39
00:02:16.150 --> 00:02:19.840
This represents this transition from targeting what is druggable to

40
00:02:19.880 --> 00:02:23.260
