00:17:58.310 --> 00:18:04.770
Because

302
00:18:04.810 --> 00:18:06.600
we are hide from the

303
00:18:07.850 --> 00:18:10.450
immune system, so we will not cause the

304
00:18:11.170 --> 00:18:12.610
anti-drug problem.

305
00:18:15.310 --> 00:18:16.170
Okay. Thank you.

306
00:18:16.710 --> 00:18:16.990
Thank you.

307
00:18:24.720 --> 00:18:28.540
Okay, moving on now to the next presenter, who

308
00:18:28.580 --> 00:18:32.300
will be Michelle Kriner from Wayfinder

309
00:18:32.360 --> 00:18:35.940
Biosciences, who's going to talk about a potent orally bioavailable small

310
00:18:36.020 --> 00:18:39.740
molecules that inhibit c-MYC translation and suppress tumor

311
00:18:39.780 --> 00:18:40.940
growth in vivo.

312
00:18:42.560 --> 00:18:46.530
Yeah. Hi. Thank you to the organizers for this opportunity,

313
00:18:47.860 --> 00:18:49.500
and I have no disclosures.

314
00:18:51.780 --> 00:18:55.060
So I'm really happy to be here today to introduce you to Wayfinder

315
00:18:55.140 --> 00:18:58.700
Biosciences and our approach for going after

316
00:18:58.740 --> 00:19:02.260
undruggable protein targets by targeting the

317
00:19:02.340 --> 00:19:03.540
mRNAs that encode them.

318
00:19:04.660 --> 00:19:08.320
So specifically, we are developing orally available small

319
00:19:08.360 --> 00:19:11.840
molecules that can bind to regulatory RNA

320
00:19:11.880 --> 00:19:15.760
elements and disrupt their function such that the

321
00:19:15.780 --> 00:19:18.840
undruggable protein target is not produced in the first place.

322
00:19:20.580 --> 00:19:23.620
And the way that we find these molecules is based on a

323
00:19:23.660 --> 00:19:27.580
technology that was developed by our co-founders during and

324
00:19:27.660 --> 00:19:30.430
after their PhDs at the University of Washington in

325
00:19:30.480 --> 00:19:34.120
Seattle. And this technology enables us to convert

326
00:19:34.840 --> 00:19:38.680
RNA structure modulation into an easily readable fluorescent

327
00:19:39.060 --> 00:19:39.360
signal.

328
00:19:40.440 --> 00:19:44.080
And so essentially what we're able to do is isolate

329
00:19:44.260 --> 00:19:47.080
RNA structures of interest from a target mRNA,

330
00:19:48.100 --> 00:19:51.620
encode them into our Wayfinder platform, and screen small

331
00:19:51.680 --> 00:19:55.580
molecule libraries against these RNA targets to

332
00:19:55.620 --> 00:19:59.440
identify molecules that are able to bind to our

333
00:19:59.480 --> 00:20:03.130
target of interest and stabilize its structure in a manner that is

334
00:20:03.140 --> 00:20:06.380
selective for that RNA over other RNA targets.

335
00:20:07.820 --> 00:20:11.140
And so for the proof of concept of this platform, we

336
00:20:11.160 --> 00:20:14.900
wanted to go after a very high-value undruggable target.

337
00:20:15.110 --> 00:20:19.020
And so obviously MYC really rose to the top of that list, and that's what

338
00:20:19.040 --> 00:20:21.060
I'm going to present to you today.

339
00:20:22.180 --> 00:20:25.620
So MYC should need no introduction to this audience.

340
00:20:26.440 --> 00:20:30.050
It is arguably the most important undruggable protein left in cancer,

341
00:20:30.520 --> 00:20:33.800
and there's a massive opportunity to impact patients in

342
00:20:33.859 --> 00:20:35.660
diverse indications.

343
00:20:37.160 --> 00:20:40.960
But unfortunately, there has been a lot of failure in this space because MYC

344
00:20:41.000 --> 00:20:44.880
really does have the perfect storm of undruggable properties.

345
00:20:45.000 --> 00:20:46.429
So as a transcription factor,

346
00:20:47.400 --> 00:20:50.910
its protein structure is quite disordered and there's no catalytic

347
00:20:50.940 --> 00:20:52.040
pocket to target.

348
00:20:52.960 --> 00:20:56.860
In addition, biologics can't access the protein because it's in the

349
00:20:56.900 --> 00:20:57.420
nucleus.

350
00:20:58.600 --> 00:21:02.180
And MYC is very important for the proliferation of healthy

351
00:21:02.190 --> 00:21:05.530
cells and is also very rarely mutated in cancer,

352
00:21:06.180 --> 00:21:10.179
making it very difficult to develop selective targeted therapies.

353
00:21:11.840 --> 00:21:15.630
And so at Wayfinder, we believe that targeting the mRNA of

354
00:21:15.900 --> 00:21:19.260
MYC can address these issues with drugging the

355
00:21:19.280 --> 00:21:22.900
protein. And in addition, we have

356
00:21:23.680 --> 00:21:24.780
discovered a mechanism

357
00:21:25.840 --> 00:21:29.800
whereby targeting a regulatory circuit that's only used under certain

358
00:21:29.880 --> 00:21:33.520
conditions in cells can actually give us a way to selectively target

359
00:21:33.940 --> 00:21:35.900
tumor cells over healthy cells.

360
00:21:38.260 --> 00:21:42.209
So the way that we began this program was inspired by the literature.

361
00:21:43.010 --> 00:21:46.920
So there have been reports of an IRE-like element in the MYC 5'

362
00:21:47.180 --> 00:21:51.090
UTR, whereby RNA structures can regulate translation of

363
00:21:51.120 --> 00:21:53.400
the MYC open reading frame under stress conditions.

364
00:21:54.260 --> 00:21:57.640
And so we chose three RNA motifs within this 5'

365
00:21:57.940 --> 00:21:58.680
UTR region

366
00:21:59.700 --> 00:22:03.300
and encoded them into our Wayfinder sensors

367
00:22:03.900 --> 00:22:07.880
and screened these against a library of 50,000

368
00:22:08.620 --> 00:22:10.560
diverse drug-like small molecules.

369
00:22:11.760 --> 00:22:14.820
And through this effort, we were able to identify four

370
00:22:14.880 --> 00:22:18.520
unrelated compounds that were able to

371
00:22:18.660 --> 00:22:22.620
significantly reduce c-MYC protein levels in a highly MYC-amplified

372
00:22:23.000 --> 00:22:24.220
mesothelioma cell line.

373
00:22:25.580 --> 00:22:28.660
And from these, we chose to proceed with

374
00:22:28.900 --> 00:22:31.519
WDC-198 for optimization.

375
00:22:33.460 --> 00:22:35.420
So we set up a hit-to-lead screening funnel,

376
00:22:36.460 --> 00:22:39.870
whereby analogs of WDC-198 were first

377
00:22:40.040 --> 00:22:43.739
tested for their ability to bind to our MYC mRNA target in our

378
00:22:43.780 --> 00:22:44.860
Wayfinder sensor assay,

379
00:22:45.720 --> 00:22:49.180
followed by assessing their ability to repress MYC protein

380
00:22:49.200 --> 00:22:51.180
levels through an HTRF assay,

381
00:22:52.000 --> 00:22:55.600
and also looking at their cellular potency by CTG assay.

382
00:22:56.960 --> 00:23:00.420
Importantly, we did see very good correlation between these

383
00:23:00.820 --> 00:23:04.700
three characteristics throughout the series, which is really important.

384
00:23:05.160 --> 00:23:08.280
In the RNA space, we don't really have the benefit of structure-guided drug

385
00:23:08.320 --> 00:23:12.180
discovery and development. So we're really doing this the old-fashioned way.

386
00:23:13.840 --> 00:23:17.830
And so our initial compound, WDC-198, had

387
00:23:18.000 --> 00:23:20.819
a cellular potency of about one micromolar.

388
00:23:20.840 --> 00:23:24.620
And over the course of eight months and about 200 compounds, we were

389
00:23:24.660 --> 00:23:27.280
able to improve the potency over one hundredfold

390
00:23:28.200 --> 00:23:31.900
to yield this compound, WDC-623, that has

391
00:23:31.960 --> 00:23:33.900
single-digit nanomolar potency.

392
00:23:34.600 --> 00:23:38.100
And this is the compound that we have now moved into in vivo studies.

393
00:23:40.760 --> 00:23:44.480
So WDC-623 and other compounds related to it are

394
00:23:44.540 --> 00:23:47.400
quite potent in multiple solid tumor types.

395
00:23:48.540 --> 00:23:52.480
So we are hoping that we will have broad applicability in many types of

396
00:23:52.520 --> 00:23:53.220
solid tumors.

397
00:23:55.680 --> 00:23:59.100
Importantly, if cells do not express the MYC mRNA,

398
00:23:59.840 --> 00:24:02.100
our series is much, much less potent.

399
00:24:02.940 --> 00:24:06.800
So here I'm showing some data we collected with an earlier compound in the series

400
00:24:07.080 --> 00:24:11.060
where we tested its potency in NCI-H1836

401
00:24:11.100 --> 00:24:14.500
cells, which are an L-MYC amplified SCLC, and compared that

402
00:24:15.020 --> 00:24:18.220
to our workhorse cell line, NCI-H82, which is a c-MYC

403
00:24:18.260 --> 00:24:20.280
amplified SCLC. And we saw

404
00:24:21.280 --> 00:24:25.260
a greater than hundredfold difference in potency between these two cell lines, and

405
00:24:25.280 --> 00:24:28.950
our compound also did not reduce L-MYC protein levels in

406
00:24:29.100 --> 00:24:29.900
H1836

407
00:24:29.920 --> 00:24:33.652
cells.So our compound

408
00:24:33.712 --> 00:24:37.372
acts very rapidly. Within 30 minutes, we see

409
00:24:37.412 --> 00:24:40.962
significant reduction of Myc protein levels, and this is

410
00:24:40.992 --> 00:24:44.632
consistent with our proposed mechanism of inhibiting translation

411
00:24:44.692 --> 00:24:48.472
initiation, followed by normal turnover of the Myc protein, which has

412
00:24:48.532 --> 00:24:49.892
about a 30-minute half-life.

413
00:24:51.192 --> 00:24:54.972
Importantly, we do not see the same effect for other short half-life proteins,

414
00:24:55.712 --> 00:24:57.452
such as RPL15, shown here.

415
00:24:58.672 --> 00:25:02.512
The effect of our compound is fully reversible upon compound washout,

416
00:25:03.292 --> 00:25:06.692
and we do not affect levels of the Myc mRNA

417
00:25:06.752 --> 00:25:10.672
transcript in these cells, which is also consistent with a

418
00:25:10.712 --> 00:25:12.152
translational mechanism.

419
00:25:15.092 --> 00:25:18.812
So we were really excited to look at the proteome-wide effects of our compound and

420
00:25:18.892 --> 00:25:21.912
see that repression of cMyc is the dominant effect.

421
00:25:22.542 --> 00:25:26.412
So this is an experiment where we treated NCI-H82 cells

422
00:25:26.452 --> 00:25:29.152
for two hours with our compound at 20 nanomolar.

423
00:25:30.572 --> 00:25:33.592
And we see that by label-free mass spec, we

424
00:25:33.632 --> 00:25:36.891
detected about 9,000 proteins with high confidence.

425
00:25:37.132 --> 00:25:40.582
And of those, cMyc and its direct transcriptional targets,

426
00:25:41.052 --> 00:25:44.932
CDC25A and B, were the most strongly repressed proteins.

427
00:25:45.172 --> 00:25:48.682
So this is really exciting validation of the selectivity of our

428
00:25:48.752 --> 00:25:49.232
compounds.

429
00:25:52.012 --> 00:25:55.572
So as we move towards in vivo studies, we needed to look at

430
00:25:55.632 --> 00:25:58.512
the ADME and PK properties of our compounds.

431
00:25:59.352 --> 00:26:02.632
Our original hit, WDC198, had pretty

432
00:26:02.672 --> 00:26:04.682
good ADME properties to start with.

433
00:26:05.472 --> 00:26:08.852
Very soluble, lipophilic, et cetera, but

434
00:26:09.692 --> 00:26:13.632
it was very unstable in the liver. And so this was an area that

435
00:26:13.652 --> 00:26:14.512
we needed to improve.

436
00:26:15.572 --> 00:26:19.232
We did identify a structural liability that we were able to

437
00:26:19.272 --> 00:26:21.852
correct and improve the stability of these compounds.

438
00:26:23.792 --> 00:26:27.472
And so with WDC623, we are able to get

439
00:26:27.532 --> 00:26:30.672
sufficient exposure to accommodate twice-daily

440
00:26:30.772 --> 00:26:32.572
dosing of our compound,

441
00:26:33.432 --> 00:26:36.392
although we still do have more work to do on the PK.

442
00:26:37.332 --> 00:26:39.812
But we thought that this was good enough to at least try a proof of concept

443
00:26:39.872 --> 00:26:41.112
experiment in vivo.

444
00:26:43.552 --> 00:26:47.452
So we did a CDX study with the NCI-H82 small cell

445
00:26:47.492 --> 00:26:51.392
lung cancer model, and we were really excited to see that five mgs per

446
00:26:51.452 --> 00:26:52.972
kg twice daily dosing,

447
00:26:54.032 --> 00:26:54.612
oral dosing,

448
00:26:55.712 --> 00:26:59.372
gave us statistically significant inhibition of tumor growth.

449
00:27:00.652 --> 00:27:03.832
And importantly, we did not see any body weight loss or clinical

450
00:27:03.872 --> 00:27:07.792
observations during this study. So this was really the first proof

451
00:27:07.832 --> 00:27:08.042
that our

452
00:27:09.012 --> 00:27:12.232
compounds and our mechanism are functional and tolerable in vivo.

453
00:27:15.592 --> 00:27:19.432
So I mentioned at the beginning that potency is really not enough when it

454
00:27:19.472 --> 00:27:23.172
comes to Myc. We really need selective ways

455
00:27:23.252 --> 00:27:27.192
to only target Myc in the cancer cells and try not to hit

456
00:27:27.232 --> 00:27:29.511
the healthy cells that also depend on Myc.

457
00:27:30.672 --> 00:27:34.552
And so we think we have a way that we can address this with our

458
00:27:34.612 --> 00:27:35.172
compounds.

459
00:27:36.092 --> 00:27:39.641
So pretty early in the development, we noticed that the activity of our

460
00:27:39.712 --> 00:27:42.272
compounds was somewhat media dependent,

461
00:27:43.452 --> 00:27:46.132
and we were able to isolate a single nutrient

462
00:27:47.172 --> 00:27:48.972
that was responsible for this effect.

463
00:27:49.421 --> 00:27:53.412
And so I'm showing a western blot here, where in every lane, the cells were

464
00:27:53.432 --> 00:27:55.602
treated with the same concentration of our compound,

465
00:27:56.512 --> 00:27:59.832
but we're titrating the levels of this single nutrient.

466
00:28:00.952 --> 00:28:04.832
And at high levels of the nutrient, which do correspond to normal blood levels of

467
00:28:04.872 --> 00:28:05.972
the nutrient,

468
00:28:06.912 --> 00:28:10.272
our compound is essentially inactive at repressing Myc levels.

469
00:28:11.532 --> 00:28:15.232
But if we reduce the nutrient levels to levels that are similar to that

470
00:28:15.272 --> 00:28:17.302
found in solid tumor microenvironments,

471
00:28:18.132 --> 00:28:20.052
our compound becomes very active against Myc.

472
00:28:20.981 --> 00:28:24.972
And so we are hoping that we can set up a system where we

473
00:28:25.032 --> 00:28:27.532
can deliver these compounds orally, and that

474
00:28:28.652 --> 00:28:32.132
in nutrient-rich normal tissues, they will not affect

475
00:28:32.452 --> 00:28:36.392
Myc in normal cells. But in nutrient-poor environments, such

476
00:28:36.432 --> 00:28:40.192
as solid tumors, cMyc will be downregulated and the cancer cells will

477
00:28:40.232 --> 00:28:40.512
die.

478
00:28:42.112 --> 00:28:45.932
And so in order to sort of test this idea

479
00:28:46.452 --> 00:28:50.212
for our next in vivo study, we wanted to look at a

480
00:28:50.312 --> 00:28:54.252
model that was poorly vascularized to really emphasize

481
00:28:54.712 --> 00:28:56.752
the nutrient depletion in solid tumors.

482
00:28:57.572 --> 00:29:00.272
And we also wanted to look in large tumors

483
00:29:01.112 --> 00:29:04.932
because we thought that would be a nutrient-limited environment as well.

484
00:29:06.012 --> 00:29:09.932
And also that's a much more realistic and difficult environment for testing

485
00:29:09.972 --> 00:29:10.602
therapeutics.

486
00:29:11.652 --> 00:29:15.312
So we did a study in the MiaPaCa2

487
00:29:15.372 --> 00:29:16.332
model of PDAC.

488
00:29:17.152 --> 00:29:20.972
And in this study, we did not dose until all of the tumors had

489
00:29:21.012 --> 00:29:23.182
reached 600 cubic millimeters or larger.

490
00:29:24.052 --> 00:29:27.672
And we were super excited to see in this study that we saw tumor

491
00:29:27.692 --> 00:29:31.312
regression with an average of 125% TGI.

492
00:29:32.132 --> 00:29:35.982
And again, importantly, there was no clin obs or weight loss observed during this

493
00:29:35.992 --> 00:29:36.332
study.

494
00:29:37.372 --> 00:29:41.252
So we think that this is a really exciting result that we're going to

495
00:29:41.292 --> 00:29:45.212
follow up on as soon as we can, and hopefully we'll get even better

496
00:29:45.252 --> 00:29:47.252
as we improve the PK properties of our compound.

497
00:29:49.452 --> 00:29:52.392
We also did look in the blood of the mice from the PDAC study,

498
00:29:53.292 --> 00:29:57.152
and we see no evidence of anemia, thrombocytopenia, or

499
00:29:57.192 --> 00:29:58.032
bone marrow dysfunction.

500
00:29:58.952 --> 00:30:00.392
We do see a little bit of lymphopenia,

501
00:30:01.292 --> 00:30:04.632
but this has been a major challenge in the field of Myc-targeting therapies.

502
00:30:04.972 --> 00:30:05.952
And so we think this is

503
00:30:06.812 --> 00:30:10.612
at least a good hint that we are sparing normal cells and really

504
00:30:10.672 --> 00:30:12.732
focusing on targeting the tumor cells.

505
00:30:14.532 --> 00:30:18.272
So with that, I will thank our investors and our funding sources.

506
00:30:20.572 --> 00:30:24.352
Our SAB members as well have developed many small molecule drugs

507
00:30:24.392 --> 00:30:27.932
previously, so they've been great to help us for doing this our first time.

508
00:30:28.332 --> 00:30:31.112
Special shout out to Nick Terret, who is our medicinal chemist.

509
00:30:32.572 --> 00:30:35.252
And this is the team at our lab in Seattle.

510
00:30:36.312 --> 00:30:37.972
Thank you, and I'm happy to take any questions.

511
00:30:43.282 --> 00:30:46.981
All right. Thank you, Michelle. Use the microphones if you have questions, please.

512
00:30:49.502 --> 00:30:52.662
Hi. Maybe I missed it. There was something regarding the

513
00:30:52.822 --> 00:30:56.562
deregulation of MYC within two hours from the first

514
00:30:56.602 --> 00:30:59.712
administration. Sorry, treatment of cells, I think that was-

515
00:30:59.742 --> 00:31:00.342
Yeah.

516
00:31:00.362 --> 00:31:03.842
But you also showed some MYC targets at two hours.

517
00:31:04.462 --> 00:31:07.402
So I was just wondering how quickly that can happen.

518
00:31:07.502 --> 00:31:10.022
Are those MYC targets also

519
00:31:10.982 --> 00:31:13.572
short-lived? Because you are looking at protein levels, I assume.

520
00:31:13.622 --> 00:31:17.202
Yeah. So I showed CDC25A and B, which

