00:37:19.862 --> 00:37:21.982
immune-mediated tumor rejection.

635
00:37:23.142 --> 00:37:26.102
And again, as a reminder, this is immuno-oncology, so these are wild-type mice

636
00:37:26.222 --> 00:37:30.122
bearing mouse-derived tumors, and we are sort of releasing

637
00:37:30.162 --> 00:37:32.762
a brake on the immune system to reject that tumor.

638
00:37:34.942 --> 00:37:38.922
So CIBL B is an interesting protein in that through

639
00:37:38.962 --> 00:37:40.322
its regulatory mechanism.

640
00:37:41.262 --> 00:37:44.422
In its inactive state, it's folded up on

641
00:37:44.462 --> 00:37:47.642
itself and is incapable of binding a

642
00:37:50.042 --> 00:37:51.722
ubiquitin-loaded E2 ligase.

643
00:37:53.502 --> 00:37:56.982
But the tyrosine kinase binding domain contains an SH2

644
00:37:57.022 --> 00:38:00.832
domain that when it binds to a phospho substrate, pushes it

645
00:38:00.902 --> 00:38:04.622
into an open conformation that can then be phosphorylated

646
00:38:04.742 --> 00:38:08.592
on a particular tyrosine 363, thus locking

647
00:38:08.622 --> 00:38:12.422
it in the open conformation and allowing a

648
00:38:13.042 --> 00:38:16.262
ubiquitin-loaded E2 to bind for subsequent

649
00:38:16.322 --> 00:38:18.762
ubiquitination and degradation of substrates.

650
00:38:20.842 --> 00:38:24.652
So with this understanding of the regulatory

651
00:38:24.702 --> 00:38:28.662
mechanism, we were able to design assays for high-throughput screening

652
00:38:28.702 --> 00:38:30.782
to look for inhibitors of CIBL B.

653
00:38:33.982 --> 00:38:37.482
The first assay that I'm going to describe today is what we call the phospho-CIBL

654
00:38:37.622 --> 00:38:40.692
assay. So this assay was charged with

655
00:38:41.282 --> 00:38:43.122
closed state inactive CIBL B

656
00:38:44.122 --> 00:38:47.162
tagged with a fluorophore through streptavidin.

657
00:38:48.142 --> 00:38:52.082
And then we added a ZAP70 peptide and Src kinase

658
00:38:52.222 --> 00:38:52.802
and ATP.

659
00:38:53.822 --> 00:38:54.262
Excuse me.

660
00:38:55.222 --> 00:38:57.042
And in this case, Src kinase does double duty.

661
00:38:57.092 --> 00:39:00.802
It first phosphorylates the ZAP70 peptide, which then serves as the substrate

662
00:39:00.882 --> 00:39:04.802
peptide, pushing CIBL into the open conformation, which can

663
00:39:04.822 --> 00:39:07.982
then be further phosphorylated by Src kinase.

664
00:39:08.702 --> 00:39:12.402
And then detection is through FRET with an anti-phosphotyrosine antibody.

665
00:39:14.282 --> 00:39:18.042
Now, of course, this assay will also discover Src kinase inhibitors,

666
00:39:18.182 --> 00:39:19.662
so in every well, we had

667
00:39:21.422 --> 00:39:25.082
a parallel screen for just ZAP70

668
00:39:25.162 --> 00:39:27.142
peptide phosphorylation,

669
00:39:28.402 --> 00:39:31.402
so that we could weed out kinase inhibitors from our assay.

670
00:39:33.112 --> 00:39:36.972
We also had an orthogonal E2 binding assay as

671
00:39:37.122 --> 00:39:40.651
a further measure of validation. And in this case, we switched

672
00:39:40.682 --> 00:39:44.662
the FRET partners. We put the terbium on the streptavidin,

673
00:39:45.302 --> 00:39:47.782
and this time had a fluorescently labeled

674
00:39:48.622 --> 00:39:51.672
E2-loaded ubiquitin ligase, so we could look for FRET sort of in the other

675
00:39:51.702 --> 00:39:54.222
direction. It helps us weed out artifacts.

676
00:39:56.002 --> 00:39:59.892
So with these assays, we screened a small library

677
00:39:59.922 --> 00:40:02.422
of 250,000 compounds at a single point

678
00:40:03.322 --> 00:40:04.882
concentration, 10 micromolar.

679
00:40:05.882 --> 00:40:09.662
And hits were defined as any compound that inhibited more than 20%

680
00:40:09.742 --> 00:40:13.162
of CIBL activity and less than 20% of Src

681
00:40:13.172 --> 00:40:14.262
kinase activity.

682
00:40:15.152 --> 00:40:16.842
That's shown here in the yellow box.

683
00:40:18.522 --> 00:40:21.042
From this assay, we got 1,100

684
00:40:21.922 --> 00:40:25.562
hits, which were manually filtered for

685
00:40:25.602 --> 00:40:29.302
properties and diversity. PAINS were removed, things like that.

