699
00:41:19.402 --> 00:41:21.762
sensogram showing one-to-one stoichiometry.

700
00:41:25.882 --> 00:41:29.842
This compound was racemic in our library, so we proceeded to resolve it into its

701
00:41:29.882 --> 00:41:33.642
two enantiomers. And we were gratified to find that all of the activity

702
00:41:33.682 --> 00:41:35.342
resides in one of the two enantiomers.

703
00:41:35.402 --> 00:41:38.642
Again, this is another measure of specific binding to the target.

704
00:41:39.642 --> 00:41:43.582
And those data are shown here. No activity for the wrong enantiomer, and all of the

705
00:41:43.642 --> 00:41:46.342
activity is in the S enantiomer.

706
00:41:49.322 --> 00:41:53.262
So crystallography revealed the binding mode of this compound, and

707
00:41:53.302 --> 00:41:54.482
it binds to

708
00:41:55.702 --> 00:41:59.402
a pocket that's sort of at the center of the closed state conformation,

709
00:42:00.302 --> 00:42:03.002
where the three domains of the protein come together.

710
00:42:04.242 --> 00:42:07.902
So this is tyrosine 363. That's the

711
00:42:08.142 --> 00:42:10.582
critical tyrosine that gets phosphorylated in the open state.

712
00:42:11.202 --> 00:42:15.002
And this molecule forms a nice pi stack with that tyrosine, as well

713
00:42:15.122 --> 00:42:15.442
as

714
00:42:16.262 --> 00:42:18.722
several important hydrogen bonds in the triazoles.

715
00:42:18.842 --> 00:42:20.982
One is water-mediated to a backbone

716
00:42:21.862 --> 00:42:25.762
of this helix over here, and then another direct hydrogen bond to another

717
00:42:25.782 --> 00:42:27.582
tyrosine on the other side of the pocket.

718
00:42:30.682 --> 00:42:34.262
Additionally, we form a third hydrogen bond with a backbone

719
00:42:34.362 --> 00:42:38.242
NH and a couple of hydrophobic interactions on the

