737
00:43:40.498 --> 00:43:44.318
So what you can see is that if we extend the hydrophobic group a little bit with

738
00:43:44.398 --> 00:43:48.278
a CF3 or cyclopropyl, we pick up improved interactions with the lysine

739
00:43:48.318 --> 00:43:50.678
that's right there, the hydrophobic part of the lysine.

740
00:43:52.378 --> 00:43:55.818
Removing the sulfur from this linker dramatically increases the

741
00:43:55.898 --> 00:43:57.038
metabolic stability.

742
00:43:58.098 --> 00:44:01.818
And then finally, getting rid of the chiral center with this oxetane allows us to

743
00:44:01.858 --> 00:44:05.798
pick up another water-mediated hydrogen bond in the back pocket for an

744
00:44:05.838 --> 00:44:07.318
additional increase in potency.

745
00:44:09.118 --> 00:44:12.738
And as a measure of compound properties here, I've shown the lipophilic ligand

746
00:44:12.798 --> 00:44:14.158
efficiency, which is sort of a

747
00:44:15.318 --> 00:44:19.038
